aglona.caption: Driving from 56°N 27°E towards the 🇧🇾 🇱🇻 🇷🇺 tripoint, passed through the town of Aglona and saw the Cirīša lake from the road. There was a nice little urban park with a pier made from shipping crates. Pulled over and jumped right in!
aglona.name: Aglona

ally.caption: Tiny little pond near the village of Ally, about an hour walk from the farm.
ally.name: Ally

brigenes-ezers.caption: After the surreal Ignalina nuclear power station and the 🇧🇾 🇱🇻 🇱🇹 tripoint, wanted to decompress. Found this lake with a lovely dock right off the road, and went for a nice twilight swim.
brigenes-ezers.name: Briġenes Ezers

burtnieki.caption: After visiting the north point of Latvia and 58°N 25°E, I wanted to go for one last swim before turning in the rental car. Found this lake with a dock that was along my route. Turns out they were having a race and many of the streets were closed, so wound up running to the lake and back. Still had an ideal swim with some seagulls.
burtnieki.name: Burtnieki

camp-compass.caption: Compass sent 800 of us to a summer camp in upstate New York to act like kids for three days. I got up early both mornings and went for a swim in the lake. Saw a deer and a lizard.
camp-compass.name: Camp Compass

cannonsville.caption: Went for a swim at sunset in this reservoir. There were many stone cairns.
cannonsville.name: Cannonsville

congamond-lakes.caption: Parked the van in a quiet parking lot so I could wake up and go for a swim from the pier here.
congamond-lakes.name: Congamond Lakes

conquest-road.caption: Went for a night swim on the Delaware seashore.
conquest-road.name: Conquest Road

cronce.caption: Went for a dip in this little stream after a long walk to a deep valley.
cronce.name: Cronce

croncelorbe.caption: Another spot where I went for a dip in the Cronce after a long walk.
croncelorbe.name: Croncelorbe

daugava.caption: On the way from the northern point of Lithuania to a bunch of Struve points, parked the car at a bus stop and found a nice place to walk down to the Daugava river.
daugava.name: Daugava

daugavpils-fortress.caption: Stayed in an art museum inside one of Europe’s best preserved fortresses. Saw on the map that there was a pier in the river, so walked through the ramparts, over the dyke and down to the water. Beautiful nighttime city view. Met a cat.
daugavpils-fortress.name: Daugavpils Fortress

dechantlacke.caption: Popular spot near Vienna for wild swimming. Had to trespass through an abandoned train yard.
dechantlacke.name: Dechantlacke

devils-slide.caption: One of the most beautiful beaches near Silicon Valley, on the Pacific Coast Highway just north of Half Moon Bay. There’s a small parking lot and a long wooden staircase to get to the bottom of the cliff.
devils-slide.name: Devil’s Slide

didziosios-lapes.caption: To other confluence seekers who couldn’t get to this point because it was in a lake, I say you’re doing it wrong. Hiked through some farmland to find this beautiful lake, then swam out to the exact confluence point. Lesson learned: all parts of the bank look the same when the lake is surrounded by reeds.
didziosios-lapes.name: Didžiosios Lapės

donauinsel.caption: Went for a little swim at three different points around this island in the middle of the Danube. Whole northern tip of the island is FKK.
donauinsel.name: Donauinsel

dublin-pond.caption: Parked the van here one night so that I could wake up in the morning and step right into the lake for a swim.
dublin-pond.name: Dublin Pond

dysnai.caption: Stopped here to relax after visiting the rather dismal eastern point of Latvia. Ignored sign that said no trespassing. Found some guy sitting in his car and I asked, “Можно плавать?” He nodded, “Да.” Left my clothes in the car and walked down to the water.
dysnai.name: Dysnai

einbi.caption: After checking in to my hotel in a traditional country estate, thought I would visit the western point of Estonia at sunset. Parked at the gate of a private house then walked to the coast. Found an abandoned Soviet building. Went for a quick dip in the sea, which was shallow so I walked out and sat on one of these large rocks.
einbi.name: Einbi

fatnas-island.caption: This palm island in the middle of a lake in Siwa Oasis was developed as a desert paradise. During covid we found it entirely abandoned and ours to explore.
fatnas-island.name: Fatnas Island

filicijanavas.caption: Crossing from Poland back into Lithuania on a dirt road, I saw a lakeside vacation home with a sauna in a trailer and a nice little dock. Jumped in the lake and swam back over to the Polish side. My first international swim!
filicijanavas.name: Filicijanavas

fjaðra.caption: Stayed in this remote vacation home car from any mobile phone signal. Went for a long walk in the evening on the bouncy moss with my hat and gloves to keep me warm. Went for a swim in the nearby river which was glacially cold. Washed my hair and found I could rince it in the current in two seconds. Swam to an island in the middle covered in blueberries.
fjaðra.name: Fjaðrá

fluðir.caption: Nice to watch the steam rising out of this nice warm rectangular lake.
fluðir.name: Flúðir

fort-foster.caption: Went for a dip in the ocean at the southern point of Maine!
fort-foster.name: Fort Foster

grimaldi.caption: We were hiking from Menton to Ventimiglia, and went for a dip in this lovely pebble beach. A little further on we found this little isolated cove and were like, let’s do it!
grimaldi.name: Grimaldi

großer-brombachsee.caption: Driving across Europe during a heat wave without air conditiong, stopped here for a jump in the water to cool off!
großer-brombachsee.name: Großer Brombachsee

großer-muggelsee.caption: On the way from Berlin to Poland, took the S-Bahn and the tram to the Großer Müggelsee. No witches here!
großer-muggelsee.name: Großer Müggelsee

haapsalu.caption: The ferry to Estonia’s western islands leaves from here. Found a quiet spot on the north end of town where I could park the car and hop right in the water.
haapsalu.name: Haapsalu

hino.caption: After visiting the 🇪🇪 🇱🇻 🇷🇺 tripoint and crossing into Estonia, I found a place with access to Lake Hino. It was quite muddy, but looking through the trees I spied dock! Eventually I found a hidden trail made of boards that led to the secret dock, which had two rowboats and some benches.
hino.name: Hino

hreppslaug.caption: This pool near Borgarnes is practically as far north as I've ever been. Had a bunch of algae growing in it but was fed by a pipe of warm water.
hreppslaug.name: Hreppslaug

hveragerði.caption: A local nature guide told us where to find a naturally hot river in the middle of a glacial valley! We hiked for an hour though every imaginable weather extreme and mud that wanted to suck our boots off. Put all our clothes in trash bags so they wouldn't get soaked. The natural hot river was blissful, and you could find your ideal temperature between freezing and boiling by moving a few centimeters.
hveragerði.name: Hveragerði

jurmala.caption: Went for a long walk along the beach but found it mostly empty, except for kitesurfers enjoying the phenomenal wind. Walked around the mouth of the Lielupa and found a lovely little swimming spot where the water was calm. Someone had collected some mushrooms and left them on a bench.
jurmala.name: Jūrmala

kileleshwa.caption: We lived in Nairobi for five weeks, and our Airbnb had a pool surrounded by a lush tropical garden. With monkeys.
kileleshwa.name: Kileleshwa

kipsalas-pludmale.caption: On my way to the Kipsala Pool, I found this beach right at the foot of the Vanšu Bridge. There was a bench right by the water, so went for a quick dip before continuing to the pool.
kipsalas-pludmale.name: Ķīpsalas Pludmale

kisezere-pludmale.caption: On my way to the Mežaparks pool, thought I would go for a dip in Lake Ķīšezers. Found a wooded peninsula with several docks. Couldn’t resist this one!
kisezere-pludmale.name: Ķīšezere Pludmale

kupiskenu-starkenas.caption: After a long day of playing Baltic Bingo, found a charming campground on the shore of Kupiškio Tvenkinys Lake. There were stone stairs leading from my cabin down to the pier, so I went for a dip before bed and another at sunrise with my morning tea.
kupiskenu-starkenas.name: Kupiškėnų Starkėnas

lake-chaubunagungamaug.caption: This lake is a bit of a tourist trap because of the long name, and they wanted $10 for parking. Went for a little trek through the woods and found this nice isolated spot with access to the water.
lake-chaubunagungamaug.name: Lake Chaubunagungamaug

lake-lauderdale.caption: On my way to Albany, found this lake with a little beach.
lake-lauderdale.name: Lake Lauderdale

lake-liepaja.caption: After visiting the Karosta naval base, I discovered a park with a causeway extending into Lake Liepāja. I hiked to this observation tower, where I discovered a little boat pier...
lake-liepaja.name: Lake Liepāja

le-riad.caption: Sauna with a tiny swimming pool, big enough to do like three strokes. Counts as swimming.
le-riad.name: Le Riad

luisen-brunnen.caption: Climbing over huge boulders in the Felsenlabyrinth Luisenburg and visiting 50°N 12°E made me want to find some water. My topographic map took me to this tiny pond fed by a spring. Was a bit muddy but got the job done.
luisen-brunnen.name: Luisen Brunnen

mezaparks.caption: Went for a second swim in the same lake at the beach. There was a boat rental stand with a bored looking guy sweeping the leaves. Didn't give me a look when I walked through the gate and went for a swim at the end of the pier. Water was cold but the sun was nice when I got out. Went to the cafe and had a terrible hamburger.
mezaparks.name: Mežaparks

neringa.caption: I drove down the Curonian Spit as far as you can go before getting to the border zone, labeled as an ecological preservation area. Beach was empty as it was quite windy. Wasn’t going to try to swim to Russia... not yet.
neringa.name: Neringa

piscinas-bernat-picornell.caption: This swimming pool was built for the 1992 Olympic Games.
piscinas-bernat-picornell.name: Piscinas Bernat Picornell

quality-inn-mount-vernon.caption: Stayed in this motel on the way back from the San Juan Islands.
quality-inn-mount-vernon.name: Quality Inn Mount Vernon

ritiniu-tvenkinys.caption: 55°N 23°E happens to be right off the dam of an artificial lake. I got within 15 meters of the confluence point, which was in a thicket. Found a nice place to access the lake directly from the car. Dried off in the driver’s seat because there were so many mosquitoes!
ritiniu-tvenkinys.name: Ritinių Tvenkinys

rokiskis.caption: Was driving from Latvia back into Lithuania to finish up a few more places, and saw a lake parallel to the road. Walked down to the river, jumped in and went for another international swim. Loads of mosquitoes, had to get my clothes back on in a hurry!
rokiskis.name: Rokiskis

sagsjon.caption: Visiting Jeremiah I went for a swim the lake here on three consecutive days. Went first time with friends and family. Second time in the early morning, when I saw someone at a little sauna on the other side jump in the water. Then finally as I was leaving on my way to catch the bus to the airport.
sagsjon.name: Sågsjön

san-gregorio-creek.caption: Went on a camping trip to San Gregorio with my freshman dorm my first week at Stanford. After visiting the beach, went skinny dipping for the first time in the creek in total blackness. Only found out later that I’d shared the experience with people I hadn’t even become friends with yet.
san-gregorio-creek.name: San Gregorio Creek

scheveningen.caption: Rollerbladed to the beach in Scheveningen many times when I lived in Den Haag.
scheveningen.name: Scheveningen

seljavallalaug.caption: You have to hike for an hour through a beautiful glacial valley to get to this concrete pool built into the side of a hill. Where else can you enjoy rainbows and waterfalls and all this nature while swimming in a warm rectangular pool with a changing room?
seljavallalaug.name: Seljavallalaug

singliser-see.caption: Met a Polish lady in the lake who insisted on taking my picture. “Splash the water like this!” I think she said.
singliser-see.name: Singliser See

smiltyne.caption: Most people take the pedestrian ferry from Klaipėda to get here, so I felt weird driving to the edge of the beach. There’s a map that shows all the zones where you can do various things, but it was a moot point because it was so cold and windy that the beach was empty.
smiltyne.name: Smiltynė

stone-lake.caption: Stayed at this lovely B&B with its own lake. Borrowed a rowboat and rowed around the lake for a while. Went for a swim in the evening, the middle of the night and the morning.
stone-lake.name: Stone Lake

vistytis.caption: This town is a the north end of a lake bisecting Russia and Lithuania. Drove to where the road ends at a closed border post. Then found this rickety pier near the last house, with a bench, changing cubicle and helpful flag to remind you which country you’re in. Swam to within a few meters of Russia.
vistytis.name: Vištytis

wizajny.caption: After crossing into Poland on the way to the 🇱🇹 🇵🇱 🇷🇺 tripoint, stopped for a little swim in this lake. Wanted to make sure I was cooled off and ready for all that razor wire.
wizajny.name: Wiżajny

zalesjes-ezers.caption: After adventures with the border police following me around the 🇧🇾 🇱🇻 🇷🇺 tripoint and the eastern point of Latvia, wanted to relax with a little swim! Found this spot with a covered spring by the lake.
zalesjes-ezers.name: Zaļesjes Ezers
